snippet.textDisplay: In Islamic sufism there are many seats. Like the peer tarikat, the sheikh, syed, haali, muhadas ( not to be confused with muhadis of Hadiths ), haqyakdaan. Then there are non sufi seats like Mujadad, aalim, mufti, maulana etc. however Qalandar is not a single man's name. It was a sufi title. Rarest of them All. For it you have to reach a certain form of sufism. While there were many peers from the 12 silsilas (lineage). There were only 2.5 Qalandars in the history. 1st being Madhu Laal hussein, one referred in this song. 2nd being Buu Ali. And the third considered the half is the female Rabiya Basri. She is half because no female mystic reached such a level. But as she did, she had to be considered. The half part is not an insult but kind of a unique tribute to her.
